_simon"><persName>Wiesenthal, Simon</persName><linkGrp><link type="desc" target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-003219"/></linkGrp><note><p>Polish-Austrian Holocaust survivor, architect, writer. From the day of his liberation from the concentration camp Mauthausen onwards, he made it his life's task to find Nazi war criminals and collaborators and bring them to justice. His creed in this battle was ”Justice, not Revenge”, as one of his many books is called. He was also committed to combating post-war anti-Semitism, as well as commemorating the Holocaust and educating young people.
                                </p></note></person></listPerson><listPlace><place><placeName>Mauthausen concentration camp</placeName><location><geo>48.25751 14.50089</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/11185525/mauthausen-concentration-camp.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauthausen-Gusen_concentration_camp"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Buchach</placeName><location><geo>49.06234 25.39496</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="http://www.geonames.org/711348/buchach.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buchach"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Poland</placeName><location><geo>52 20</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Prague</placeName><location><geo>50.08804 14.42076</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prague"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Lviv</placeName><location><geo>49.83826 24.02324</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="http://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lviv"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Warsaw</placeName><location><geo>52.22977 21.01178</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warsaw"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Lackie Wielkie concentration camp</placeName><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1741"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Przemysl concentration camp</placeName><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1829"/></linkGrp></place